title: For Sale/Trade:  Cigarette rifle 98 mauser
postcontent: what we have  is a cigarette mauser rifle made in Erfurt  Germany maybe after ww1 these were made between 1918-36.  this is the small ring 98 mauser in 8x57 .323 bore.  why is it called a cigarette rifle the gunsmiths after ww1 had to make money and they had to take a 98 mauser and rework them over and trade to the Gis for 2 cartons of cigarettes and they would trade for food or for other things that way.  the gunsmiths would do very fine work on them because it would show how good they were.   this gun is not your run of the mill mauser alot of work went to this gun and it shows my pics just don't do it justice. this gun is in mint shape the bore looks like new all the work was done in Germany along time ago.  will trade for other guns.  thanks Todd
